<subSubSection pageId="240" pageNumber="241" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="240.[151,1437,150,321]" pageId="240" pageNumber="241">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[267,503,186,213]" pageId="240" pageNumber="241" refId="ref368401" refString="Rondani, C. (1857) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: II. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars prima. Oestridae: Syrphfidae [sic!]: Conopidae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 264 pp., 1 pl. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1857">Rondani (1857: 158)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1857" box="[626,893,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="240" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedemontana">
<emphasis box="[626,893,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="240" pageNumber="241">Cheilosia pedemontana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from just the female sex without specifying the exact 
<taxonomicName box="[266,352,223,249]" family="Number" pageId="240" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
of specimens, but giving a single measurement of length: “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="240" pageNumber="241">Foeminam tantum speciei mihi Prof. Bellardi transmisit</emphasis>
[Prof. Bellardi sent to me only the female of the species]”. He attributed the species name to L. Bellardi. 
<bibRefCitation author="Claussen, C. &amp; Thompson, F. C." box="[335,722,295,321]" pageId="240" pageNumber="241" pagination="275 - 281" refId="ref348016" refString="Claussen, C. &amp; Thompson, F. C. (1996) Zur Identitat und Synonymie der von Camillo Rondani beschriebenen Cheilosia - Arten (Diptera, Syrphidae). Studia Dipterologica, 3, 275 - 281." type="journal article" year="1996">Claussen &amp; Thompson (1996: 280)</bibRefCitation>
considered the single MZUF female as the 
<typeStatus box="[1211,1313,295,321]" pageId="240" pageNumber="241">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
